clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For decreasing blood clotting Often used along with heparin for treatment of deep vein thrombosis

contraindications.disease: LD sub 50 sub 233 mg kg orally in mice LD sub 50 sub 250 mg kg orally in rats
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Dicumarol is an coumarin like compound found in sweet clover It is used as an oral anticoagulant and acts by inhibiting the hepatic synthesis of vitamin K dependent coagulation factors prothrombin and factors VII IX and X
